rComments: This class was pretty interesting as a whole. The 8am lectures with Philpott were a little boring to say the least, but he realized it was boring too, so he cancelled a lot. You should probably just stay in bed. The final presentation was pretty fun, and watching him react to what some people presented was hilarious, especially if they were stupid.

Way cool guy. He's from England, which makes the common phrases he uses exponentially funnier. He's the kind of dude you could see having a beer with. It's a pity his class is at 8:00am -- I would have preferred to be awake for his lectures, since they were on-point and told you what you needed to know.

Philpott is a very good teacher for the ME 170 course. He really knows his material and is very helpful. He tries to put a lot of necessary material in the lectures which are difficult at 8 am. Throws pop quizes once in a while. Important to go to lectures. They will pay off in the long run.

First of all; Very hot british accent. 8am class, but the sound of the accent keeps me awake. Hes a great teacher. If you go to him for extra help, he is very keen on helping. And he definetly sound like he knows his stuff!
Great guy, very approachable. Hard to stay awake at 8am lecture, but most of the learning is done in the lab anyway. Always hear only good things about him.

Well he is a really nice guy, has a great british accent, and will talk to you if you want to talk to him about ANYTHING.  Only thing is that in ME 170 almost all learning is done in the lab so his part in the process is minimal and hard to stay awake during if you have it early in the morning.
Nice guy, he puts his everything into the class. Experienced Fellow.
Good lecturer, but tough to stay awake at 8am.  This class is mostly learned in the lab, but Philpott tries to explain the difficult parts at class.

The class is fun, but the lectures are very dry. Just try and stay awake. He'll throw pop quizzes at you for attendance purposes in lecture, so go. Really cool guy who will always help you out if you need it.
His lectures are boring as hell but, having worked with him in the Ford Lab, I can personally say he's a really cool guy.
